upload.js is a file uploader webapp Ã  la gmail file attachment uploader. The files are stored locally in the filestore/ directory.

The following dependencies are mandatory; use npm 1.0.17 or better and run from the project root:
npm install formidable
npm install nodeunit
npm install zombie
npm install express
npm install connect-form
npm install jade

Runs successfully on node 0.4.10

To execute the tests, execute: 
	node_modules/.bin/nodeunit spec/*.js
	
The tests cover the storage (file system)

To run the web server, execute:
	node controller/index.js

Then hit http://localhost:8099

Tested on Safari 5.1, Chrome v12.0, Firefox 5.0 and IE 9.
